for external command seat \u002B 1st person view mods. Maybe a rover console, lander console...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs this possible?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you make an entire plugin for it, then yes it is feasible.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DrunkenKerbalnaut","CreatedById":169550,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-09T11:54:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222880772\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022153240\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221481278931\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022114736\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JPLRepo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, JPLRepo said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nProps (stock) will only work if part of an InternalModel.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks for the heads up. It felt like a rabbit hole, that\u0027s why I ask \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo.... \u00A0What defines \u0022Internal Model\u0022? Is it relevant only to a kerbal-is-in-a-command-pod game state? I guess I\u0027m asking for a primer. I\u0027ll check more tutorials.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks again!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RA3236","CreatedById":150734,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-09T11:55:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222880824\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022153240\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221481284450\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022169550\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DrunkenKerbalnaut\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, DrunkenKerbalnaut said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks for the heads up. It felt like a rabbit hole, that\u0027s why I ask \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo.... \u00A0What defines \u0022Internal Model\u0022? Is it relevant only to a kerbal-is-in-a-command-pod game state? I guess I\u0027m asking for a primer. I\u0027ll check more tutorials.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks again!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nInternal Model means in IVA only (basically what you just said)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DrunkenKerbalnaut","CreatedById":169550,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-09T11:57:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222880825\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022153240\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221481284505\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150734\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022RA3236\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, RA3236 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nInternal Model means in IVA only (basically what you just said)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo if I could trigger \u0022IVA\u0022 from an external command chair, as opposed to the current EVA-like behavior?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEDIT: which I guess would amount to building an IVA - as bare as it may be - for the external command chair, so it could filter the props as viewable. I think. Idk.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-12-09T14:08:12Z\u0022 title=\u002212/09/2016 02:08  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 9, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by DrunkenKerbalnaut\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RA3236","CreatedById":150734,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-09T11:58:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222880826\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022153240\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221481284632\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022169550\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DrunkenKerbalnaut\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, DrunkenKerbalnaut said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo if I could trigger \u0022IVA\u0022 from an external command chair, as opposed to the current EVA-like behavior?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n... ill let a proper modder answer that question.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DrunkenKerbalnaut","CreatedById":169550,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-09T11:59:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u002